{
    "proposal": {
        "title": "Add Specs: FLARE",
        "description": "Adding new specification support for relaying Flare data on Lava. Flare's C-Chain is an EVM-compatible coreth fork (go-flare = avalanchego + coreth). The spec imports ETH1 and adds coreth-specific eth_*/txpool_* methods plus the extended coreth debug namespace. The trace_* (OpenEthereum) and ERC-4337 bundler add-ons are disabled because coreth/go-flare does not implement them. Note: debug_* and txpool_* methods are supported by coreth on nodes configured with the appropriate API flags but are gated on the public free-tier endpoint.",
